rne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Swynford was born before 1406, in England, his father, Sir Thomas Swynford, was 38 and his mother, Joan Crophill, was 32. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Lady Elizabeth Beauchamp. He died on 8 January 1440, in Kettlethorpe, Lincolnshire, England."},"et":{"before 1406–8 January 1440":"enne 1406–8. jaanuar 1440","1394–Female":"1394–Surnud","1394–Male":"1394–Surnud","1405–1478":"1405–1478","1406–1440":"1406–1440","1406–1428":"1406–1428","1411–1482":"1411–1482","1417–1467":"1417–1467","1425–1475":"1425–1475","1435–1498":"1435–1498","1367–1432":"1367–1432","1373–1411":"1373–1411","4 November 1435":"4. november 1435","1440":"1440","1373":"1373","1482":"1482","1394":"1394","before 1406":"enne 1406","1425":"1425","2 April 1432":"2. aprill 1432","1435":"1435","1467":"1467","1478":"1478","1411":"1411","1367":"1367","8 January 1440":"8. jaanuar 1440","1432":"1432","1498":"1498","1475":"1475","1386":"1386","1417":"1417","1428":"1428","1406":"1406","1405":"1405","Kettlethorpe, Lincolnshire, England":"Kettlethorpe, Lincolnshire, England","Northall, Buckinghamshire, England":"Northall, Buckinghamshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"before 1406–8 January 1440":"ennen vuotta 1406–8. tammikuuta 1440","1394–Female":"1394–Kuollut","1394–Male":"1394–Kuollut","1405–1478":"1405–1478","1406–1440":"1406–1440","1406–1428":"1406–1428","1411–1482":"1411–1482","1417–1467":"1417–1467","1425–1475":"1425–1475","1435–1498":"1435–1498","1367–1432":"1367–1432","1373–1411":"1373–1411","4 November 1435":"4. marraskuuta 1435","1440":"1440","1373":"1373","1482":"1482","1394":"1394","before 1406"